President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate John P. Howard III and Vijay Shanker as Associate Judges on the District of Columbia Court of Appeals. John P. Howard III currently serves as an Administrative Law Judge at the District of Columbia Office of Administrative Hearings, where he handles cases for various District of Columbia agencies. Prior to this, he served as an Administrative Law Judge for the District of Columbia Commission on Human Rights and worked in private practice. He holds a B.A. from Howard University and a J.D. from Georgetown University Law Center. 

Vijay Shanker is currently the Senior Litigation Counsel in the United States Department of Justice, Criminal Division, and serves as Deputy Chief of the Appellate Section. Before joining the Department of Justice, he worked in private practice in Washington, D.C. at Mayer Brown, LLP, and Covington & Burling, LLP. He clerked for Judge Chester J. Straub on the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit after graduating from the University of Virginia School of Law, where he was a Notes Editor for the Virginia Law Review and a member of the Order of the Coif.